'''Assane Diao''' (born 7 September 2005) is a Senegalese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Serie A]] club [[Como 1907|Como]] and the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].

==Club career==
===Betis===
Diao is a youth product of [[CD Badajoz|Badajoz]], Flecha Negra and Balón de Cádiz, before moving to the youth academy of [[Real Betis]] in 2021, on a contract until 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eldesmarque.com/futbol/real-betis/20230330/assane-diao-la-reconversion-en-delantero-del-ultimo-canterano-que-se-ha-entrenado-con-pellegrini_161338003.html|title=Assane Diao: la reconversión en delantero del último canterano que se ha entrenado con Pellegrini|first=Javi|last=Carbonero|date=30 March 2023|website=ElDesmarque}}</ref> Originally a midfielder, his attacking skills led to him being molded into a left [[winger (association football)|winger]], and he started playing with [[Betis Deportivo Balompié|the reserves]] in the [[Segunda Federación]] in 2022.<ref name="auto1">{{Cite web|url=https://en.as.com/soccer/liverpool-and-leipzig-circling-for-betis-pearl-diao-n/|title=Liverpool and Leipzig circling for Betis pearl Diao|first=Andy|last=Hall|date=6 July 2023|website=Diario AS}}</ref>

On 26 July 2023, Diao extended his contract with the club until 2027.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.estadiodeportivo.com/futbol/betis/mejor-noticia-posible-con-assane-diao-20230726-424628.html|title=La mejor noticia posible con Assane Diao|date=26 July 2023|website=Estadio Deportivo}}</ref> He made his senior and professional debut with the ''Verdiblancos'' as a late substitute in a 1–0 [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] loss to [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] on 21 September 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sevilla.abc.es/alfinaldelapalmera/noticias-betis/assane-diao-debut-valiente-20230921000034-nts.html|title=Assane Diao, un debut valiente|date=22 September 2023|website=ABC de Sevilla}}</ref> Later that month, on 28 September, he scored his first goal on his [[La Liga]] debut in a 1–1 away draw against [[Granada CF|Granada]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/de/news/granada-1-1-real-betis-boye-y-diao-dejan-en-tablas-un-entretenido-partido-en-el-nuevo-los-carmenes-38298694 |title=Granada 1-1 Real Betis: Boyé y Diao dejan en tablas un entretenido partido en el Nuevo Los Cármenes |publisher=OneFootball |language=es |date=28 September 2023 }}</ref> A week later, on 5 October, he netted his first goal in European competitions in a 2–1 victory over [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.in/football/match/_/gameId/687650/sparta-prague-real-betis |title=Real Betis 2-1 Sparta Prague |publisher=ESPN |date=5 October 2023 }}</ref> On 7 December, after coming on as a substitute, he scored his second La Liga goal, a 90+4' equalizer in a 2-2 draw against [[FC Barcelona]].

===Como===
On 7 January 2025, Betis announced Diao's transfer to Italian [[Serie A]] side [[Como 1907]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realbetisbalompie.es/noticias/actualidad/el-real-betis-y-el-como-1907-llegan-a-un-acuerdo-para-el-traspaso-de-assane-diao-30910|title=El Real Betis y el Como 1907 llegan a un acuerdo para el traspaso de Assane Diao|trans-title=Real Betis and Como 1907 reach an agreement for the transfer of Assane Diao|publisher=Real Betis|language=es|date=7 January 2025|accessdate=7 January 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ariadi |first=Nana |date=2025-01-07 |title=Como 1907: Official Club Statement |url=https://comofootball.com/en/como-1907-official-club-statement-2/ |access-date=2025-01-07 |website=Como 1907 |language=en-US}}</ref> The fee was reported at around €12 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-07 |title=Official: Como sign 19-year-old Diao from Real Betis |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/official-como-sign-19-old-164000716.html |access-date=2025-01-07 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> On 23 February 2025, Diao scored a 77th minute goal vs [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]] to secure a 2–1 win vs the league leaders. As a result, [[Inter Milan]] overtook Napoli in the table.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://football-italia.net/serie-a-como-2-1-napoli-inter-thank-diao/|title=Como 2-1 Napoli – Inter have Diao to thank|last=Young|first=Peter|access-date=23 February 2025|date= 23 February 2025|website=Football Italia}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Senegal, Diao moved to Spain at the age of three and has dual citizenship. He played for the nation's [[Spain national under-19 football team|under-19 team]] at the [[2023 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]].<ref name="auto1"/>

On 19 March 2025, Diao's request to switch international allegiance to Senegal was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-Change">{{Cite web |title=FIFA Change of Association Platform |url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform |accessdate=19 March 2025 |website=knowledge.fifa.com}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Originally a [[midfielder]], Diao is a strong, and powerful [[winger (association football)|winger]] who excels at crossing the ball. Primarily right-footed, he is strong with both feet. He has a powerful technique, and strong heading ability.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://www.estadiodeportivo.com/futbol/betis/alerta-betis-por-assane-diao-20230327-415858.html|title=Alerta en el Betis por Assane Diao|date=29 March 2023|website=Estadio Deportivo}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Diao has a twin brother, Ousseynou, who is also a youth footballer in Spain.<ref name="auto"/>

